<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8" />
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
  <title>BuzzMind · Privacy &amp; Policy</title>
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/shared/site.css" />
</head>
<body>
  <%- include('../partials/site-nav', { active: 'privacy' }) %>

  <header class="page-hero">
    <span class="eyebrow">Legal</span>
    <h1>Privacy &amp; <span class="grad">Policy</span></h1>
    <p class="lead">Your privacy matters to us. This page explains what we collect, why we collect it, and the choices you have.</p>
  </header>

  <section class="section tight">
    <div class="prose">
      <p class="updated">Last updated: June 1, 2026</p>

      <div class="legal-block">
        <h2>Information we collect</h2>
        <p>When you create an account we collect the name, username, and email address you provide. As you use BuzzMind we also store the quizzes, classes, assignments, and game results needed to run the platform.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="legal-block">
        <h2>How we use your data</h2>
        <p>We use your information to operate the service, personalize your dashboard, show your progress, and improve our quizzes and features. We do not use your data to build advertising profiles.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="legal-block">
        <h2>Cookies &amp; sessions</h2>
        <p>We use a single session cookie to keep you signed in securely. We do not use third-party advertising or cross-site tracking cookies.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="legal-block">
        <h2>How we share information</h2>
        <p>We never sell your personal data. Information is shared only in these limited cases:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>With your professors or institution, to deliver classes and grades.</li>
          <li>With trusted service providers that host the platform on our behalf.</li>
          <li>When required by law or to protect the safety of our users.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="legal-block">
        <h2>Your rights</h2>
        <p>You can view, edit, or delete your account information at any time from your settings page. You may also contact us to request a copy of your data or to close your account.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="legal-block">
        <h2>Data security</h2>
        <p>Passwords are stored using strong one-way hashing, and access to personal data is restricted to authorized staff. No system is perfectly secure, but we work hard to protect your information.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="legal-block">
        <h2>Questions about this policy?</h2>
        <p>If you have any questions about how we handle your data, we are happy to help.</p>
        <p style="margin-top:0.8rem"><a href="/contact" class="btn btn-primary">Contact our team</a></p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <%- include('../partials/site-footer') %>

  <script src="/shared/i18n.js"></script>
</body>
</html>
